<Base title="Custom Integrations — DH7" description="Custom software integrations for small businesses. Connect your systems so data flows where it needs to, automatically.">
  <h1>Custom Integrations</h1>

  <p>Most small businesses run on a handful of software tools that don't talk to each other. Data lives in separate places. People move it between systems by hand. Things get missed. Things get wrong.</p>

  <p>Custom integrations fix that. We connect your systems so data flows where it needs to, automatically.</p>

  <h2>What we build</h2>

  <p>Point-to-point integrations between the tools you already use — CRMs, accounting packages, booking systems, inventory tools, communication platforms. Whatever the combination, we can connect them.</p>

  <h2>Why custom?</h2>

  <p>Off-the-shelf integration tools handle simple cases. For anything more specific — your data model, your workflow, your edge cases — you need something built to fit.</p>

  <p>Custom integrations are built around your actual workflow, not a generic template. You own the code, not a SaaS subscription. There's no third-party middleware that can go down or change its pricing.</p>

  <h2>Who this is for</h2>

  <p>Small businesses that have outgrown manual processes. If you're copying and pasting data between systems, re-entering information, or spending time on reconciliation — that's time and money you don't need to spend.</p>

  <h2>Systems we work with</h2>
